2026-04-21 01:29:30 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['PSU-to-control connection pair'] hypothesis_explanation='The power supply module’s positive and negative output leads are cross‑connected to the control module’s input leads. This polarity inversion matches the symptoms: the green LED on the PSU is on (so 12 V is present), the red inverted‑cables LED on the control module is on (it is designed to light when the control module sees reversed polarity from the PSU), and the load lamp remains off because the control module and then the series diode in the load module prevent correct current flow. Correcting the polarity of the two cables between the power supply module and the control module (swapping the two conductors so PSU + goes to control + and PSU − to control −) should restore normal operation.'
